Unknown gunmen have opened fire on the convoy of Enugu State Commissioner for Lands, Hon. Chidi Aroh, killing two policemen attached to the politician. The officers killed were identified as Inspector David Adabu and Inspector Solomon. The ambush it was learnt, happened in a community in Anambra State with the gunmen engaging the escort of the commissioner in a gun battle. Aroh however escaped with his driver while the two policemen were killed. When contacted, the commissioner promised to get back to SaharaReporters as he was in a meeting. He, however, kept mute when asked to confirm the incident.